  <span id="freeText11410355526973578050" style="display:none"><b>"Deep in the cell of my heart <br />I really want to go<br />There is another world<br />There is a better world<br />Must be ..."</b> -- The Smiths<br /><br />Tonight the moon is 99%. Tomorrow it will be a full moon. Is that a sure promise?<br /><br /><b>".. his whole life had merely been a long wait in an abandoned telephone booth with a dead phone. Now there was only one solution: to leave the abandoned booth as quickly as possible!"</b><br /><br />But isn't it a LIE (Life Is Elsewhere)? A LIE syndrome! I feel this book is about the illusions that we allude to ourselves, little insignificant lives that sooner/ later fill with lies of present-past-future to save their structure! Yet amidst all these, beautiful old promise of escape that "Life is Elsewhere" (maybe around the corner)-- never ceases to exist! :(</span>
