        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2311850765" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7840812584217074974">For the majority of this book, I thought how Kundera was maybe not for me anymore, that I could still see how clever and sarcastic his work was but I just didn&apos;t feel like being thrown into the ugly pond of it all, so I wasn&apos;t going to play his game... but the last part with the inside Joke changed things and I can&apos;t help being impressed once again. Well done. <br/><br/><i>(A few days later)</i><br/>But... I&apos;m rating books mainly based on my enjoyment and it just wasn&apos;t there for the most part. I do think it is a ver</span>
  <span id="freeText7840812584217074974" style="display:none">For the majority of this book, I thought how Kundera was maybe not for me anymore, that I could still see how clever and sarcastic his work was but I just didn't feel like being thrown into the ugly pond of it all, so I wasn't going to play his game... but the last part with the inside Joke changed things and I can't help being impressed once again. Well done. <br /><br /><i>(A few days later)</i><br />But... I'm rating books mainly based on my enjoyment and it just wasn't there for the most part. I do think it is a very good book. It's definitely not for everyone; you could enjoy this if you enjoyed other Kundera's books or if you don't mind reading about insufferable characters, horribly toxic relationships and stuff like that. I guess I wasn't in the mood for this or these characters and their behavior were just too much for me to be able to enjoy the book.</span>
  <a data-text-id="7840812584217074974" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


